CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 4, 1958, pg.12 reads: Guests At Birthday Party - These many smiling faces are proof that a good time was had by all at the 16th birthday party of Karen LaRue West of New Kensington, Pa. The party, given by Karen's parents, Mr. and Mrs. Thomas L. West Jr., was held at the Greene Hearthe, Dec. 28.  The guests hailed from Pittsburgh, the surrounding areas, and Cleveland, Ohio. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of teenagers, including Karen LaRue West wearing light colored short sleeved dress with lace top, posed in Greene Hearth for sixteenth birthday party
